```jsjavascript

// Example 7: Handling errors with Fetch API

fetch("https://api.example.com/data")

.then((response) => {

if (!response.ok) {

throw new Error("Network response was not ok");

}

return response.json();

})

.then((data) => console.log(data))

.catch((error) => console.log("Error:", error));

```
